Understanding the Concept of Virtual Machine

Vm is the emulation of a computer systems and are based on the computer achitecture and provides functionality of the physical computer.

A virtual machine as define by popek and Goldberg as an efficient, isolated duplicate of a real computer machine .

The physical machine running the vm is refer to as the host and while the vm emulated on the that machine is generally referred to as the guest. A host can emulate several guest, each of which can emulate different operating systems and hardware platforms.

Virtualization was developed in 1990 and is different from simulaion and emulation. Virtualization employs technique used to create instances of an environment.
